  "doc_id": "18873",
  "text": "Empirical support for Eq. [CITATION_1] is provided by cross species comparisons. Among mammals of equivalent body size, large entropy species (bats), defined by late sexual maturity, broad reproductive span, and small litter size are relatively long lived; low entropy species (rats and mice), characterized by early sexual maturity, narrow reproductive span, and large litter size are short lived.",
