  "bib_entries": {
    "23787594": {
      "title": "Mammalian aging, metabolism, and ecology: evidence from the bats and marsupials",
      "abstract": "This study compared trends in body size, life span, metabolic rate, and ecology of bats and marsupials with those from mammals generally, using a 580 species data base. These results directly conflict with predictions of both «rate of living» and brain-size mediated theories of aging. However, they are consistent with an evolutionary theory that posits exceptionally long life spans among mammals with reduced environmental vulnerability"
